This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image super-resolution using deep learning techniques. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of 3D images, which could place it in the neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
